  {
    q: "What is export-focused SEO and how is it different from regular SEO?",
    a: "Regular SEO focuses on ranking for high-volume local or national searches. Export-focused SEO targets the lower-volume but high-intent searches that procurement managers and importers use when looking for Indian suppliers. Terms like 'ISO certified chemical manufacturer Gujarat export' or 'bulk textile supplier India MOQ 500kg' have low search volume but produce extremely valuable enquiries. We prioritise these over generic high-competition terms."
  },
  {
    q: "How should my product catalogue be structured on the website?",
    a: "The ideal structure groups products by category with a filterable grid. Each product page should include the product name, CAS number if applicable, specifications, available grades or variants, packaging options, MOQ, certifications relevant to that product, and a direct enquiry button. Downloadable spec sheets and safety data sheets add significant credibility with international buyers."
  },
  {
    q: "Should my manufacturer website be in English only or also in Gujarati or Hindi?",
    a: "For export-focused manufacturers, English is the priority. International buyers require English and a non-English website creates an immediate credibility barrier. If your business also serves domestic clients in Gujarat, we recommend a primarily English site with a Gujarati or Hindi section for local agents and distributors. For Arab markets, we can add Arabic product descriptions as part of the enterprise package."
  },
  {
    q: "How do Google Ads for B2B manufacturing work?",
    a: "We run Google Search campaigns targeting keywords used by importers and procurement managers. Ads appear when a buyer in a target country searches for a product in your category. Clicks go to dedicated landing pages matched to each product group or export market. Campaigns are structured by geography, product line, and buyer type. We track form submissions and WhatsApp contacts as conversions, not just clicks."
  },
  {
    q: "How long does it take to see results from export SEO?",
    a: "Most manufacturers see the first organic ranking improvements within 6 to 8 weeks for lower-competition export keywords. For more competitive categories, first-page rankings typically take 4 to 6 months. Google Ads produce immediate visibility from day one of launch. We recommend running both in parallel during the first 6 months."
  },
  {
    q: "We already have a basic website. Do we need to rebuild it or can you work with what we have?",
    a: "We will audit your existing website first. If the structure is sound, we can work with it, improving product pages, adding a catalogue section, fixing technical SEO issues, and improving the overall design. If the site is very old, not mobile-friendly, or built on a platform that limits what we can do, a fresh build is usually faster and more cost-effective in the long run."
  }
];
